body.html:
Chris Wayland came to us in need of rebranding and repositioning his newly acquired travel agency. Originally named Oriental Express, the company received calls for Asian take-out food daily, so it was obvious that the current branding was not attracting the right customers. Although they had many Asian clients, Chris no longer wanted the company represented in this way. We started the branding process by renaming his company to Way- port which nods to Chris’s last name Wayland and also his favorite destination: Portland.

We were inspired by the elegance and optimism that was associated with air and nautical travel in the 1960’s and saw an opportunity to niche Wayport as a professional, well-established travel agency for the modern traveler. The identity has been well received by both Chris and his customers and has also won Corporate Identity Gold in Muse Creative Awards 2018.
